Date: 14/11/1846
Source: Nelson Examiner and New Zealand Chronicle
Author:
Vol / Page: 146
Edition:
Quote: <i>No pasturage license should be granted but after submission to public competition;</i> any other system would infallibly lead to jobs, to the usurpation of immense districts by grasping adventurers without sufficient capital to stock them, and to general confusion, jealousy, and ill-will.
